An economist says the Presidential Economic Advisory Council is aware of the job crisis. JOHANNESBURG - It's only the first month of the year, and already 2020 is marred by job losses. READ: Unpacking SA's latest employment growth Mining companies, Samancor Chrome, and Glencore have become the latest companies to announce retrenchments, after Telkom and Massmart leaving thousands of workers in a vulnerable position. An economist says the Presidential Economic Advisory Council is aware of the job crisis.
Wandile Sihlobo said, "all I can say to assure our people is that there is a lot of work...We understand the constraints that are in SA...There is work underway."